<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Course Website</title>
    
    <style>
    /* CSS for the registration button */
    nav {
        text-align: center; /* Aligns the button to the center */
        margin-top: 20px; /* Creates space from the top border */
    }

    nav ul {
        padding: 0;
        list-style: none;
    }

    nav ul li {
        display: inline;
    }

    nav ul li a {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 10px 20px;
        text-decoration: none;
        background-color: #00ffe1; /* Button background color */
        color: #121212; /* Button text color */
        border-radius: 5px;
        transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s;
    }

    nav ul li a:hover {
        background-color: #f73333; /* Button background color on hover */
        color: #333; /* Button text color on hover */
    }

    </style>

    <style>
    /* Reset default margin and padding */
    * {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    /* Body and general styles */
    body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        background-color: #121212; /* Dark background color */
        color: #fff; /* White text color */
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
    }

    /* Navigation styles */
    nav ul {
        list-style: none;
    }

    nav ul li {
        display: inline;
    }

    nav a {
        text-decoration: none;
        color: #fff; /* White text color for navigation links */
    }

    /* Header styles */
    h1 {
        text-align: center;
        padding-top: 50px;
    }

    /* Main section styles */
    main {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
    }

    /* Course card styles */
    .course {
        background-color: #333; /* Darker background for course cards */
        border-radius: 8px;
        margin: 20px;
        padding: 20px;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .course h3 {
        margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .course p {
        color: #ccc; /* Lighter text color for course descriptions */
    }

    .course a {
        color: #fff; /* White text color for 'Learn More' links */
        text-decoration: none;
        border: 1px solid #fff; /* White border for the link */
        padding: 5px 10px;
        border-radius: 5px;
        transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }

    .course a:hover {
        background-color: #fff; /* Change background to white on hover */
        color: #121212; /* Change text color on hover */
    }

    /* Footer styles */
    footer {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 20px 0;
    }

    /* Animated Registration Button */
    a.registration-btn {
        display: block;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 20px auto;
        padding: 15px 30px;
        border: 2px solid #fff;
        border-radius: 25px;
        color: #fff;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-size: 18px;
        transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }

    a.registration-btn:hover {
        background-color: #fff;
        color: #121212;
        transform: scale(1.1);
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
    }

    </style>


</head>

<body>
    <nav>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="/register.hbs">Register</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <h1>Welcome to Our Course Website</h1>

    <main>
        <h2>Featured Courses</h2>

        <div class="course">
            <h3>Course 1</h3>
            <br>
            <img src="https://blogassets.leverageedu.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/23170101/List-of-Professional-Courses-after-Graduation.gif" alt="Course 1">
            <br><br>
            <p>"Computer Science Fundamentals" is an introductory course designed to provide a comprehensive understanding of the fundamental concepts and principles that underpin the field of computer science. Throughout this course, students will explore the foundational building blocks and theories that drive modern computing systems and technologies.</p>
            <br><br><br>

            <h3>Course 2</h3>
            <br>
            <img src="https://media.designrush.com/inspirations/129681/conversions/_1523543112_460_harvard-preview.jpg" alt="Course 1">
            <br><br>
            <p>Harvard University offers a free, self-paced course providing an introduction to the foundational concepts of computer science. This course is designed for individuals with or without prior programming experience, aiming to deliver a comprehensive understanding of computer science principles and practices</p>
            <br><br><br>
            <hr>
        </div>

    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2023 Course Website</p>
        <p>designed by: Rishab Rebala and Rajnish Rai</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>